<br><br>Incidentally, I presume someone has checked he's not Arantir (I asked, but I'm only L27, so...).<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aelina>Aelina</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/28/00 10:26:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Oracle of K'Arnon</span><hr size=1> book of turmoil you get from a quest in neriak.  The quest takes place entirely within the city.<br><br>Book of scale drops in two parts from Nagafen and Vox.  The parts must be reassembled by a dark elf in neriak.  This is one of the final steps in the orginal Firey Avenger quest.<br><br>With all the new FA type quests out there he may now want the other books.  When did you talk to him? <p><table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>Aelina</td></tr><tr><td>Wizard of Neriak</td></tr><tr><td>Follower of The Burning Prince</td></tr><tr><td>Cazic-Thule</td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucarlothecurious.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Carlo the Curious</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/28/00 12:01:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Oracle of K'Arnon</span><hr size=1> I talked to him yesterday. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucarlothecurious.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Carlo the Curious</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/28/00 12:21:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Oracle of K'Arnon</span><hr size=1> Also, what level do you need to be to do the book of turmoil quest, and is the book No Drop?<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uzealpath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ZealPath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/28/00 1:21:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Oracle of K'Arnon</span><hr size=1> I've done the book quest (with my DE SK, not my Eru Wiz =0), its fairly easy, should be fine at level 20. Handing in the book of Turmoil to the Oracle will have him give you &quot;A Glowing Torch&quot; 7 AC +5 Cha.<br><br>People used to do this quest for the torch (In the old days I remember seeing Enchanters with it...).<br><br>Nowadays I don't think I've seen anyone with it for around one RL year, but it should still be possible hehe. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showPrevMessage?topicID=41.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showNextMessage?topicID=41.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicI